BEGIN_SOLUTION
$BR
$BBOLD Part (a)  $EBOLD
Here 
\[\theta(B) = 1- 0.4 B = 0\]
when \(B = 2.5\). So the process is invertible. 

$BR
$BR
$BBOLD Part (b)  $EBOLD
Roots here are
\[ \frac{0.7\pm \sqrt{-0.71}}{0.6} = \frac{0.7 \pm 0.843i}{0.6}, \]
i.e., \( 1.167 \pm 1.404i. \) The magnitude of the roots is 
\[ \sqrt{1.167^2 + 1.404^2} = 1.826 > 1 \]
and so the process is invertible. 

END_SOLUTION

